text: Ināra Mūrniece (born 30 December 1970) is a Latvian journalist and politician who is Speaker of the Saeima (Latvian Parliament) since 2014. She was re- elected as Speaker on 6 November 2018 by 44 votes to 32. ==References== Category:1970 births Category:Living people Category:All for Latvia! politicians Category:National Alliance (Latvia) politicians Category:Speakers of the Saeima Category:Deputies of the 11th Saeima Category:Deputies of the 12th Saeima Category:Deputies of the 13th Saeima Category:Women deputies of the Saeima Category:21st-century Latvian women politicians
